1
00:00:10,320 --> 00:00:11,390
I give my word!

2
00:00:13,180 --> 00:00:16,360
Fall to the feet of Draupadi
and beg for forgiveness

3
00:00:18,220 --> 00:00:20,360
and the Pandavas shall consider
even that as a penance.

4
00:00:29,280 --> 00:00:31,390
Could you do so much, Prince?

5
00:00:36,350 --> 00:00:37,380
Pardon me, Krishna!

6
00:00:39,150 --> 00:00:41,130
Crime, forgiveness,
punishment, war...

7
00:00:41,150 --> 00:00:42,250
All these talks are futile.

8
00:00:43,250 --> 00:00:45,350
If you indeed wish to avoid
this great battle

9
00:00:47,150 --> 00:00:49,250
put forth a proposal
that seems reasonable.

10
00:00:50,380 --> 00:00:52,260
But can you make your friend

11
00:00:53,180 --> 00:00:56,130
comply to it, King of Anga?

12
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:01,320
I can request my friend.

13
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:04,350
I cannot order him.

14
00:01:08,350 --> 00:01:12,350
When a dog riding an elephant
barks at the king of the forest

15
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:15,280
the elephant is the one
who is blamed

16
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:20,320
for supporting the dog
with its capability.

17
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:26,260
In fact, it is your ability

18
00:01:27,220 --> 00:01:30,100
that is the base of
the Prince's tyranny.

19
00:01:35,220 --> 00:01:37,090
It is my suggestion to you

20
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:41,230
that you give up your alliance
to the Prince.

21
00:01:43,180 --> 00:01:46,100
Only that shall make up
for your sins

22
00:01:46,250 --> 00:01:49,060
and grant a new leash of life
to your friend.

23
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:56,320
I have faith in your virtue.

24
00:01:57,080 --> 00:02:00,060
And my faith is
my virtue, Krishna.

25
00:02:04,250 --> 00:02:07,230
Rather than betraying my friend

26
00:02:08,220 --> 00:02:10,130
I would choose to die.

27
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:22,220
I respect you, King of Anga!

28
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:32,250
So I shall make

29
00:02:34,150 --> 00:02:35,130
a final effort.

30
00:02:42,220 --> 00:02:46,030
No forgiveness,
no punishment.

31
00:02:47,220 --> 00:02:50,030
No kingdoms,
no wealth.

32
00:02:52,150 --> 00:02:57,030
Give the Pandavas free reign
over five towns, Your Majesty.

33
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:01,120
Just five towns!

34
00:03:02,050 --> 00:03:05,000
[TENSE MUSIC]

35
00:03:20,980 --> 00:03:21,960
Friend!

36
00:03:22,220 --> 00:03:27,030
I find this proposal by Krishna
acceptable.

37
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:33,160
This is deceit, King of Anga.

38
00:03:35,220 --> 00:03:36,220
This is deceit.

39
00:03:38,050 --> 00:03:41,220
Krishna wants to get
the Pandavas

40
00:03:41,950 --> 00:03:43,160
freedom to rule

41
00:03:44,150 --> 00:03:48,030
by getting them five towns.

42
00:03:53,020 --> 00:03:56,000
After attaining
the freedom to rule

43
00:03:56,020 --> 00:04:00,160
the sons of Pandu
can challenge us for battle.

44
00:04:05,020 --> 00:04:07,020
[LAUGHING]

45
00:04:07,950 --> 00:04:11,090
Therefore, Krishna

46
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:13,920
under any circumstances

47
00:04:14,050 --> 00:04:17,900
wants to pit the hundred
sons of King Dhﬂtarashtra

48
00:04:19,020 --> 00:04:21,090
against the five Pandavas

49
00:04:21,980 --> 00:04:24,990
in the battlefield.

50
00:04:31,950 --> 00:04:35,900
Without any help from
Grandsire Bheeshma

51
00:04:35,950 --> 00:04:37,900
and Grandmaster Drona.

52
00:04:41,950 --> 00:04:42,950
King of Gandhar.

53
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:46,900
If the sons of Dhritarashtra
are faced with the Pandavas

54
00:04:46,950 --> 00:04:50,950
I shall stand at the forefront
as their shield.

55
00:04:54,980 --> 00:04:58,990
I approve of this peace proposal
only to avoid this great war.

56
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:01,120
Not to protect myself.

57
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:07,860
The Pandavas are giving up
authority for peace.

58
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:11,920
You could at least give up
arrogance, Duryodhan.

59
00:05:14,020 --> 00:05:14,990
Prince.

60
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:19,050
Krishna speaks wisely.

61
00:05:20,850 --> 00:05:22,920
Accept to the proposal
of five towns.

62
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:29,930
King Dhritarashtra,
the right is yours!

63
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:31,890
Please accept it.

64
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:38,020
Grant the sons of Pandu
free reign over five towns.

65
00:05:46,950 --> 00:05:47,980
Duryodhan, my son.

66
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:56,060
Accept this peace proposal,
my lad.

67
00:05:59,980 --> 00:06:01,990
Liberate the entire clan

68
00:06:03,020 --> 00:06:05,090
from the gravity
of this battle, son.

69
00:06:09,950 --> 00:06:12,830
Spare your parents
from this pain, son.

70
00:06:32,050 --> 00:06:33,820
Five towns!

71
00:06:34,050 --> 00:06:37,860
Shall I concede my defeat
by giving up five towns?

72
00:06:41,850 --> 00:06:44,890
Shall I accept

73
00:06:44,980 --> 00:06:46,860
that I fear those Pandavas?

74
00:06:46,950 --> 00:06:49,760
- No!
- Father

75
00:06:49,850 --> 00:06:53,020
if a stone
is thrown at a dog and a lion

76
00:06:54,020 --> 00:06:57,020
the dog barks at the stone

77
00:06:58,920 --> 00:06:59,990
and the lion

78
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:03,950
roars at the ones who threw it!

79
00:07:06,750 --> 00:07:09,920
Will I ever be afraid
of the thought of war?

80
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:10,920
Will I?

81
00:07:11,850 --> 00:07:14,960
- Impossible!
- No, son...

82
00:07:14,980 --> 00:07:19,930
And this isn't a question
of wealth or authority.

83
00:07:20,850 --> 00:07:24,800
This is a matter of
personal rivalry, father!

84
00:07:29,850 --> 00:07:33,960
As long as the sons of Pandu
are breathing on this earth

85
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:37,830
the entire atmosphere

86
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:41,720
seems to be poisoned
to me, father.

87
00:07:46,850 --> 00:07:50,890
I would rather embrace
a foul smelling bull.

88
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,890
But I cannot grant five towns
to the Pandavas.

89
00:07:54,850 --> 00:07:59,700
I can grant an adulterous woman
the status of a wife.

90
00:07:59,780 --> 00:08:02,890
But I cannot grant five towns
to the Pandavas.

91
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:06,930
I can behead myself before Yam Raj!*
*Yama or Yamaraja, the god of death.

92
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:10,890
But I cannot grant five towns
to the Pandavas!

93
00:08:36,850 --> 00:08:38,850
Listen, Krishna.

94
00:08:39,850 --> 00:08:41,850
Forget about five towns

95
00:08:43,680 --> 00:08:45,820
I won't give the Pandavas

96
00:08:47,780 --> 00:08:51,820
even a chunk of land

97
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:53,890
spanning the tip of a needle.

98
00:08:54,650 --> 00:08:55,820
I won't!

99
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:14,720
Think for the last time before
making a decision, Prince.

100
00:09:15,820 --> 00:09:20,730
Because when you see your
destiny closing in upon you

101
00:09:22,650 --> 00:09:25,860
I hope you do not have to run
to protect yourself.

102
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:32,850
Prince.

103
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:36,720
When an owl cannot
compel the sun to set

104
00:09:36,850 --> 00:09:38,830
it closes its eyes

105
00:09:39,650 --> 00:09:41,860
and imagines
that the sun has set.

106
00:09:43,820 --> 00:09:47,760
You are overlooking the gravity
of the situation yet to arise.

107
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:53,560
Are you not confident about
your abilities, Grandsire?

108
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:57,560
Braver than you

109
00:09:57,850 --> 00:10:02,590
was King Virat of
that little Piscean nation

110
00:10:04,850 --> 00:10:08,560
who had not waved
his banner of surrender

111
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:12,560
even before my entire army.

112
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:15,720
Because the Pandavas
are your rivals.

113
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:18,750
Not just the Pandavas.

114
00:10:18,780 --> 00:10:21,700
Even the supreme Yadava
Krishna is their ally.

115
00:10:23,580 --> 00:10:26,590
Do not forget it, Duryodhan.

116
00:10:26,780 --> 00:10:28,660
Master Drona.

117
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:32,660
Does your soul quiver

118
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:34,590
even looking at an unarmed man?

119
00:10:39,620 --> 00:10:41,750
What greatness is this?

120
00:10:44,780 --> 00:10:47,520
I shall assuage your worry

121
00:10:47,650 --> 00:10:50,560
right this very moment.

122
00:10:53,620 --> 00:10:54,650
[YELLING]
Soldiers!

123
00:11:42,550 --> 00:11:46,520
Soldiers, arrest this shepherd!

124
00:11:57,580 --> 00:11:58,720
Will you arrest me?

125
00:12:01,620 --> 00:12:03,600
Duryodhan, you fool!

126
00:12:06,680 --> 00:12:09,420
Make this attempt as well.

127
00:12:15,660 --> 00:12:19,510
Duryodhan, do not
commit this mistake!

128
00:12:20,660 --> 00:12:25,610
- Dhritarashtra, stop your son!
- Duryodhan! Son!

129
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,670
Wait, son! Wait!

130
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:30,700
Duryodhan, what injustice
is this?

131
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:35,470
Duryodhan, you may die
this very moment.

132
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:40,600
No!

133
00:12:43,430 --> 00:12:45,500
I cannot end his life.

134
00:12:46,660 --> 00:12:50,510
Brother Bheem is the one
who has sworn to slay him!

135
00:12:55,630 --> 00:12:58,670
King of Gandhar,
fulfill your strategy!

136
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:03,480
Shackle my wrists!

137
00:13:27,460 --> 00:13:29,410
[CHAIN RATTLING]

138
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:50,540
[SOLDIERS GROANING]

139
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:25,340
Foolish soldiers!
Get up!

140
00:14:26,430 --> 00:14:28,470
Shackle his wrists!

141
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:30,440
Get up!

142
00:14:56,560 --> 00:14:58,540
Soldiers!

143
00:15:36,460 --> 00:15:39,340
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

144
00:15:55,330 --> 00:15:59,510
Your soldiers cannot bear the
weight of your sins, Duryodhan!

145
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:05,240
Only you have to
commit this deed.

146
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:07,330
Pick up the shackles!

147
00:16:08,430 --> 00:16:12,500
Let us see how much more burden
of sins can your soul bear?

148
00:16:15,460 --> 00:16:17,370
Flaunt your might!

149
00:16:21,260 --> 00:16:22,400
[YELLING]
Arrest me!

150
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:30,240
Duryodhan!
Son!

151
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:31,470
Wait, son!
Wait!

152
00:17:06,260 --> 00:17:08,370
[CHAIN RATTLING]

153
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:16,170
[DURYODHAN LAUGHS]

154
00:17:19,360 --> 00:17:22,210
[CONTINUE LAUGHING]

155
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:02,140
Do not do this, friend!

156
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:05,200
Such behaviour
with a messenger of peace

157
00:18:06,130 --> 00:18:07,160
isn't appropriate.

158
00:18:15,130 --> 00:18:16,370
[BOTH LAUGHING]

159
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:18,100
D-Duryodhan!

160
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,170
Move, shepherd!

